NYMEX Membership Services

May 1, 2001

Notice # MS-30


REINSTATEMENT OF MEMBERSHIP PRIVILEGES


Please be advised that effective with the close of business, May 1, 2001, the

following member(s) have reinstated their membership privileges:


Peter Sepe (SEPE-3496) as a Lessee Member with a qualified trader guarantee

provided by MBF Clearing Corp.


SWITCH OF LESSOR


Please be advised that effective with the close of business, May 1, 2001, the

following member(s) will switch their lessor within the Exchange:


Michael Frenda (MFR-6272)


Randy Rechten (RDEL-4287)


Robert Essig (STX-3371)


NOTICE OF INTENTION TO SWITCH QUALIFYING CLEARING MEMBER


 Please be advised that effective with the close of business, May 1, 2001,

Man International Inc., will no longer guarantee the following member(s):


Stephen P. Willner (SPW-247)


James Sims (JMS-7307)


 However, the above mentioned will remain a member guaranteed by Pioneer

Futures, Inc.  In connection therewith, notification of any claims against

the aforementioned individuals arising out of transactions executed on the

Exchange up to the close of business May 1, 2001, must be submitted to the

Corporate Secretary,s Office within (10) ten days.


 Members and Member Firms have (10) days from the date of this notice to

advise the Corporate Secretary,s Office of any claims in accordance with Rule

2.51.


 Inquiries regarding the above should be addressed to the Member Services

Department at 212-299-2379.


